Lighter
------------------------------------------
Lighter is a kmer-based error correction method for whole genome sequencing
data. Lighter uses sampling (rather than counting) to obtain a set of kmers
that are likely from the genome. Using this information, Lighter can correct
the reads containing sequence errors.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libgcc1-10.2.0-1
  libstdc++6-10.2.0-1
  zlib0-1.2.11-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-10.2.0-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/mourisl/Lighter

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/mourisl/Lighter/archive/v1.1.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack Lighter-1.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./Lighter-1.1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/Lighter-1.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/Lighter-1.1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(Lighter)
  /usr/bin/lighter.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/Lighter.README
  /usr/share/doc/Lighter/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/Lighter/README.md

